- Extract JSX blocks >30 lines into a separate component file under a local \`./components/\` folder.
- Prefer colocated component folders: component file + colocated test + local \`./components/\` child folder.
- For lists, memoize \`renderItem\` handlers and keep stable, non-index keys.
- Use \`useCallback\` and \`useMemo\` only when referential stability is measurably needed.

## TypeScript Specifics

- No \`any\` — use discriminated unions, generics, or \`unknown\` + type guards.
- Explicit type annotations on ALL function parameters and callback handlers.
- Functions with more than 2 params → single \`Readonly<>\` object param.
- Shared types defined once and imported everywhere — no copy-pasted type definitions.
- Avoid redundant type aliases (\`type Foo = string\`).

## Testing

- Move non-trivial logic into pure functions and test those directly. Keep component tests simple.
- Colocate tests next to source: \`foo.ts\` → \`foo.test.ts\`.

## Boundaries

- Do not introduce new dependencies without strong justification.
- Do not change design tokens or theme unless explicitly requested.
- Avoid large refactors — minimal, targeted changes only.` }) %>
